Intuition
after looking at problem i realized it is a sliding window problem and i need to find maximum lenth of subarray with 2 distinct characters , so my window size is dynamic , for this problem i will create frequency map and i need to return the size of subarray with maximum possible 2 distinct fruits.

Approach
i need 2 pointers high and low and initalize them to zero , high is used to add elements in frequency map and low is used to remove elements from frequency map ,
create empty dictionary freq = {} , so store the frequency of elements in subarray ,
initalize max_fruits = 0 (in case there are no elements in array)

now we traverse the array loop condition
for high in range(len(fruits)):
add elements into the frequncy map as frequency map is currently empty
freq[fruits[high]] = freq.get(fruits[high] , 0) + 1
check for case when len(freq) > 2 :
remove elements from frequency till it comes to required condition that is k is equal to 2 or kess than 2
freq[fruits[low]] -= 1
if freq[fruits[low] == 0:
del freq[fruits[low]]
move low pointer low +=1

now when the case is in required condition
if len(freq) == 2 or len(freq) < 2:
calculate length of substring , length = high - low + 1
get maximum_fruits by comparing it with maximum length of subarray

return max_fruits

Complexity
Time complexity:
O(n)
Space complexity:
O(1)
Code
class Solution:
    def totalFruit(self, fruits: List[int]) -> int:
        low = 0
        high = 0 
        max_fruits = 0
        freq = {}

        for high in range(len(fruits)):
            freq[fruits[high]] = freq.get(fruits[high] , 0) + 1

            while len(freq) > 2:
                freq[fruits[low]] -= 1
                if freq[fruits[low]] == 0:
                    del freq[fruits[low]]
                low += 1
            if len(freq) == 2 or len(freq) < 2:
                length = high - low + 1
                max_fruits = max(length , max_fruits)
        return max_fruits
